## v1.2.0 (2026-07-02)

**Changed by:** 2026-07 ecosystem CI-naming rollout + ruleset pass across 13 HI repos.

**Verification:** verified-ci.

**What changed:** Folded in the FULL emit-before-require lifecycle that the v1.1.0 keystone
rename-PR was one PIECE of, now executed and verified end-to-end across 13 HI repos:
- New Overview/Verification framing: verified-ci now also covers the full lifecycle batch pass.
- New callout block (v1.2.0 addition) after the v1.1.0 name-mismatch callout.
- Extended `description` and added tags (`emit-before-require`, `emit-on-pr-branch`,
  `safest-superset-scope`, `deferred-mutation-authorization`).
- New "When to Use" trigger: batch emit-before-require ruleset pass across many repos.
- New Quick Reference step #5 (batch pass: emit-on-PR-branch confirmation, `add = canonical ∩
  emitted − already_required`, post-PUT integrity re-GET of all 6 rule types + enforcement +
  refs/heads/main condition + strict policy).
- New Detailed Steps 9–13: emit-before-require ordering across the rollout; confirm emit on PR
  branches not just main; safest-superset scope (add canonical, remove nothing); full PUT-object
  reconstruction + integrity re-verify; and the authorization boundary (broad "finish it" ≠
  override of a standing "defer" + timed-out question ≠ consent).
- Two new Failed Attempts rows (read "finish it" as authorization to run ruleset PUTs; assume the
  ruleset pass could run immediately after rollout PRs merged).
- New Verified-On row (Odysseus + 13 HI submodules; canonical test/package/install/release added
  to homeric-main-baseline; emit-on-PR-branch verified; integrity re-checked; Hephaestus excluded,
  Myrmidons no-op).

**Why:** The prior versions captured the pieces (add-a-check mechanics, require-before-it-exists,
emitted-name-vs-required-name deadlock + keystone rename-PR) but not the full lifecycle in which the
keystone rename-PR sits. This session completed and live-verified that lifecycle: after the
CI-naming rollout PRs merged so every repo EMITS canonical names on main, the deferred ruleset pass
added those names to required_status_checks via GET→append→PUT the full array across 13 repos. It
also surfaced two load-bearing lessons: confirm emit on PR BRANCHES (not just main) before requiring
to avoid an expected-but-missing deadlock, and a broad "finish it" does NOT override a standing
"defer all ruleset updates" boundary (the safety classifier correctly blocked the PUT batch until
explicit re-authorization). Same core recommendation (GET→append→PUT the full array, emit before
require) — extended, not rewritten; hence a MINOR bump.

